    {
      "id": "caead1c075eee216aa2ef3ba226e093fca0fe745",
      "author": {
        "_account_id": 117,
        "name": "Andreas Dilger",
        "email": "adilger@thelustrecollective.com",
        "username": "adilger"
      },
      "date": "2012-01-28 00:40:14.000000000",
      "message": "Patch Set 1: Looks good to me, but someone else must approve\n\nI've put a question out in LU-241 to see if anyone is in production with the existing checksum algorithm.  Since that patch was around for a long time (since 1.8.4 or so) it may be in use there already.\n\nIf that is the case, then this patch will need to be changed to include a new checksum algorithm type (deprecating the old crc32c algorithm) so that it doesn't break existing systems using it.\n\nYou may want to consider submitting a separate patch (separate Change-Id) which goes down that route, so that it can begin testing and inspection in parallel until we hear back from anyone in LU-241.",
      "accounts_in_message": [],
      "_revision_number": 1
    },
    {
      "id": "a3df7341bd7edc0c261def10c8478028b9a05d99",
      "author": {
        "_account_id": 117,
